HEADWORD: Spiders web
<hw>Spi"der's
web"</hw> }</mhw>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The silken web which is
formed by most kinds of spiders, particularly the web spun to entrap
their prey; -- also called <altname>cobweb</altname>. See
<cref>Geometric spider</cref>, <cref>Triangle spider</cref>, under
<er>Geometric</er>, and <er>Triangle</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

